content:
Killing Sarachnis
Requirements
Skills
  • High melee stats
  • 70+ for Piety recommended
Items
  • Karil's leathertop and leatherskirt
  • Crush weapon such as a Scythe of vitur, Abyssal bludgeon, Zamorakian hasta, or Sarachnis cudgel
  • Special attack weapon such as a Dragon dagger or Dragon claws
  • Food such as anglerfish, manta rays, sharks, or karambwans
  • Potions such as super combat potion, divine super combat potions, and prayer potions or super restores
  • Teleport to house tablets or Construction cape for teleporting out

    The profit rate assumes 30 kills per hour. Your actual profits may be higher or lower depending on your speed and luck.

    Strategies

    See the Sarachnis article and its strategies sub-page for information on killing Sarachnis.

    Lower level players may want to consider flicking Protect from Melee and Piety while attacking Sarachnis. Since it's likely that the player and Sarachnis will be attacking on different game ticks, 1-tick flicking is recommended. Flicking like this will greatly save on prayer potions, allowing even lower levelled players to only need 1–2 sips per kill.

    Players that aren't using the abyssal bludgeon may want to bring a weapon with a special attack to help burst down the magic-using Spawn of Sarachnis. The type of attack does not matter, as the magic spawn does not share the crush weakness that the melee spawn or Sarachnis herself have.

    Due to constantly changing prices on the Grand Exchange, some information in this article may or may not be current.
    It is strongly recommended to check the live prices on the Grand Exchange before making large investments in any method.
